WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.068 --> 00:00:07.655
[Sound effect] Announcer:
reads words on screen

2
00:00:10.586 --> 00:00:11.379
[firemen shouting]

3
00:00:11.380 --> 00:00:13.999
[sirens blaring]

4
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:15.412
Micheal: <i>After closing-</i>

5
00:00:15.413 --> 00:00:19.412
at 4 AM on April 13th.
an inferno raged-

6
00:00:19.413 --> 00:00:21.309
through Tropiks Nightclub.

7
00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:23.171
<i>Before then-</i>

8
00:00:23.172 --> 00:00:24.654
<i>the building was in good shape.</i>

9
00:00:24.655 --> 00:00:26.034
No faulty wiring.

10
00:00:26.793 --> 00:00:27.448
Gas lines-

11
00:00:27.551 --> 00:00:29.309
<i>intact.</i>

12
00:00:29.310 --> 00:00:30.241
<i>No reason-</i>

13
00:00:30.242 --> 00:00:33.171
<i>it should erupt
suddenly and furiously-</i>

14
00:00:33.172 --> 00:00:35.067
unless by design.

15
00:00:35.068 --> 00:00:37.550
<i>The nightclub's owner.
Mr. Gene Powell here-</i>

16
00:00:37.551 --> 00:00:39.033
<i>stands accused of two charges.</i>

17
00:00:39.034 --> 00:00:41.861
Arson for Fraudulent Purpose.

18
00:00:41.862 --> 00:00:43.206
Arson-

19
00:00:44.310 --> 00:00:46.965
with Disregard for Human Life.

20
00:00:48.206 --> 00:00:50.309
I called 911 after
I saw the smoke.

21
00:00:50.310 --> 00:00:52.205
But before the
firefighters could arrive-

22
00:00:52.206 --> 00:00:53.482
Mr. Powell came out-

23
00:00:54.310 --> 00:00:56.481
just stood there
and watched it burn.

24
00:00:56.482 --> 00:00:57.688
The defendant will suggest-

25
00:00:57.689 --> 00:01:01.930
he is simply the victim
of a random attack.

26
00:01:01.931 --> 00:01:03.757
Yet-

27
00:01:03.758 --> 00:01:05.619
with so much to lose-

28
00:01:05.620 --> 00:01:07.931
he had so much to gain.

29
00:01:09.172 --> 00:01:11.102
My Financial Crimes Unit-

30
00:01:11.103 --> 00:01:14.171
noted frequent inconsistencies
in Mr. Powell's books-

31
00:01:14.172 --> 00:01:17.412
to the tune of $1.2
million in back taxes.

32
00:01:17.413 --> 00:01:19.688
The insurance payout
for the nightclub fire-

33
00:01:19.689 --> 00:01:21.550
is about double that amount.

34
00:01:21.551 --> 00:01:24.481
Backed into a
corner. Mr. Powell-

35
00:01:24.482 --> 00:01:27.136
<i>set that fire deliberately.</i>

36
00:01:27.137 --> 00:01:28.965
There is only one victim here-

37
00:01:30.103 --> 00:01:33.034
the man who perished
in that inferno.

38
00:01:34.206 --> 00:01:37.205
And that man deserves
justice here today.

39
00:01:37.206 --> 00:01:38.343
<i>Dr. Truong.</i>

40
00:01:38.344 --> 00:01:40.757
Could you please tell the
jury what your team found-

41
00:01:40.758 --> 00:01:42.033
when the fire was
finally extinguished?

42
00:01:42.034 --> 00:01:43.826
Components of accelerant bombs-

43
00:01:43.827 --> 00:01:45.688
were scattered
around the nightclub.

44
00:01:45.689 --> 00:01:49.275
<i>A concoction of volatile
chemicals and aluminum shavings.</i>

45
00:01:50.448 --> 00:01:53.550
Along with some heavily
burnt human remains.

46
00:01:53.551 --> 00:01:56.274
Now. were you able to
identify the victim?

47
00:01:56.275 --> 00:01:57.895
I'm sure there's a
family out there-

48
00:01:57.896 --> 00:02:00.585
that would like
Mr. Powell answer-

49
00:02:00.586 --> 00:02:01.999
for his crime.

50
00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:04.516
Unfortunately I can't
provide that for them.

51
00:02:04.517 --> 00:02:06.102
The few uncorrupted-

52
00:02:06.103 --> 00:02:08.378
DNA indicators we
were able pull-

53
00:02:08.379 --> 00:02:10.826
<i>were insufficient to
match to any one person-</i>

54
00:02:10.827 --> 00:02:12.067
<i>in our DNA database.</i>

55
00:02:12.068 --> 00:02:13.343
And why is that. Dr. Truong?

56
00:02:13.344 --> 00:02:14.000
<i>The accelerant bomb-</i>

57
00:02:14.001 --> 00:02:16.067
used in this blaze-

58
00:02:16.068 --> 00:02:18.516
was designed to burn
for as long as possible.

59
00:02:18.517 --> 00:02:20.585
So the body was
essentially cremated.

60
00:02:20.586 --> 00:02:22.964
Thank you. Dr. Truong.

61
00:02:22.965 --> 00:02:24.103
[observers whisper]

62
00:02:27.482 --> 00:02:29.033
Your record precedes you.

63
00:02:29.034 --> 00:02:31.516
<i>Years of experience
as Chief of Forensics.</i>

64
00:02:31.517 --> 00:02:33.171
A role with the
Major Crimes Unit.

65
00:02:33.172 --> 00:02:34.826
Yes that's all correct.

66
00:02:34.827 --> 00:02:37.619
And a good working relationship
with the Crown Attorney.

67
00:02:37.620 --> 00:02:38.964
In fact-

68
00:02:38.965 --> 00:02:39.862
weren't you at one time-

69
00:02:39.863 --> 00:02:40.999
involved intimately-

70
00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:41.655
with Mr. Billinger?

71
00:02:41.656 --> 00:02:42.999
Objection-relevance!

72
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:44.655
Sustained.

73
00:02:45.517 --> 00:02:46.517
Has Mr. Billinger-

74
00:02:46.518 --> 00:02:48.792
ever asked you to alter
your findings. Doctor?

75
00:02:48.793 --> 00:02:49.861
Judge: <i>You're treading
into dangerous waters-</i>

76
00:02:49.862 --> 00:02:50.862
Ms. Creehan.

77
00:02:50.863 --> 00:02:52.171
Where are you going with this?

78
00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:55.240
Just trying to establish why an
experienced forensic analyst-

79
00:02:55.241 --> 00:02:56.137
failed to identify the body.

80
00:02:56.138 --> 00:02:57.689
Objection Your Honour!

81
00:02:58.689 --> 00:03:00.378
I withdraw.

82
00:03:00.379 --> 00:03:02.067
No further questions.
Your Honour.

83
00:03:02.068 --> 00:03:05.068
<i>The defense calls Dr. Reva
Warner to the stand.</i>

84
00:03:05.172 --> 00:03:06.586
♪
[dramatic music]

85
00:03:11.724 --> 00:03:13.309
Dr. Warner.

86
00:03:13.310 --> 00:03:14.619
You've been a senior associate-

87
00:03:14.620 --> 00:03:17.343
at Sutherland Schmidt
Forensics for how long?

88
00:03:17.344 --> 00:03:19.171
Eight years and counting.

89
00:03:19.172 --> 00:03:20.826
Avery: <i>I appreciate
your expert insight-</i>

90
00:03:20.827 --> 00:03:22.343
<i>as an independent source.</i>

91
00:03:22.344 --> 00:03:23.930
<i>You had access to the evidence.</i>

92
00:03:23.931 --> 00:03:25.516
Did you come to any
different conclusions?

93
00:03:25.517 --> 00:03:26.619
I can't understand-

94
00:03:26.620 --> 00:03:30.413
why Dr. Truong wasn't
able to identify the body.

95
00:03:31.827 --> 00:03:34.689
He practically walked up and
introduced himself to me.

96
00:03:36.448 --> 00:03:38.723
Would you mind introducing
this court to him too?

97
00:03:38.724 --> 00:03:39.724
Meet-

98
00:03:40.310 --> 00:03:41.862
David Gallo.

99
00:03:43.586 --> 00:03:46.274
<i>Public records state he was
recently released from prison-</i>

100
00:03:46.275 --> 00:03:47.378
<i>on an arson charge.</i>

101
00:03:47.379 --> 00:03:48.792
So at this fire-

102
00:03:48.793 --> 00:03:50.586
which the defendant
supposedly set-

103
00:03:51.896 --> 00:03:53.895
there was a master
arsonist on the scene?

104
00:03:53.896 --> 00:03:56.240
Well <i>master</i> is a strong word.

105
00:03:56.241 --> 00:03:58.412
He did burn himself
up after all.

106
00:03:58.413 --> 00:04:00.550
[jury laughs]

107
00:04:00.551 --> 00:04:01.310
[judge bangs gavel]

108
00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:02.310
Order.

109
00:04:07.275 --> 00:04:09.447
♪
[dramatic percussion]

110
00:04:09.448 --> 00:04:10.448
♪
[upbeat theme music]

111
00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:18.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

112
00:04:21.965 --> 00:04:23.861
Michael: <i>Judge Costa agreed
to adjourn for the weekend.</i>

113
00:04:23.862 --> 00:04:25.742
But I'm still going to
need a miracle by Monday.

114
00:04:27.517 --> 00:04:29.205
Well what do you want
us to do about that?

115
00:04:29.206 --> 00:04:30.343
It's not a Major Crimes case.

116
00:04:30.344 --> 00:04:31.447
Charlie: <i>Yeah.</i>

117
00:04:31.448 --> 00:04:33.274
I thought you had Financial
Crimes handling this?

118
00:04:33.275 --> 00:04:34.206
Michael: <i>Yeah</i>

119
00:04:34.207 --> 00:04:35.309
<i>I thought they had
enough to convict.</i>

120
00:04:35.310 --> 00:04:37.343
But I was relying on Sarah's
testimony to seal it-

121
00:04:37.344 --> 00:04:40.309
before Reva's little surprise.

122
00:04:40.310 --> 00:04:41.447
Sarah: <i>Hold on.</i>

123
00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:42.999
I was thorough and
by the book on this.

124
00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:44.826
Thorough wasn't
enough to get results.

125
00:04:44.827 --> 00:04:47.309
It would've been helpful
to know that we had-

126
00:04:47.310 --> 00:04:48.826
<i>an arsonist on our
hands ahead of time.</i>

127
00:04:48.827 --> 00:04:49.861
It should've been impossible-

128
00:04:49.862 --> 00:04:51.964
to pull uncompromised
DNA from those remains.

129
00:04:51.965 --> 00:04:53.447
And we tried to
identify the victim-

130
00:04:53.448 --> 00:04:54.930
with the Missing
Persons Database.

131
00:04:54.931 --> 00:04:57.481
There was nothing to tie
this to Gallo until now.

132
00:04:57.482 --> 00:04:58.344
Donovan: <i>So even if Gallo-</i>

133
00:04:58.345 --> 00:04:59.861
did set the fires-

134
00:04:59.862 --> 00:05:02.033
how do we know that he
wasn't hired by Powell?

135
00:05:02.034 --> 00:05:03.861
Proving that is my only
shot at a conviction.

136
00:05:03.862 --> 00:05:06.033
I need Major Crimes' fresh eyes-

137
00:05:06.034 --> 00:05:07.205
and Rex's nose on this now.

138
00:05:07.206 --> 00:05:08.688
[Rex barks]

139
00:05:08.689 --> 00:05:10.689
What if we can't
prove it by Monday?

140
00:05:11.413 --> 00:05:12.724
Then a guilty man goes free.

141
00:05:12.827 --> 00:05:15.000
♪
[ominous music]

142
00:05:20.241 --> 00:05:21.034
Charlie: <i>Sarah.</i>

143
00:05:21.035 --> 00:05:22.344
You okay?

144
00:05:23.034 --> 00:05:23.655
Yeah.

145
00:05:23.655 --> 00:05:24.655
Yeah. I'm fine.

146
00:05:25.344 --> 00:05:27.171
[Rex whines]

147
00:05:27.172 --> 00:05:28.343
Ah. you can lie to me.

148
00:05:28.344 --> 00:05:29.206
You can't lie to Rex.

149
00:05:29.206 --> 00:05:30.000
[Rex moans]

150
00:05:30.001 --> 00:05:31.274
<i>And I mean. what
do we even know-</i>

151
00:05:31.275 --> 00:05:32.930
about this so-called
expert witness?

152
00:05:32.931 --> 00:05:33.758
Defense could have gotten

153
00:05:33.759 --> 00:05:34.964
one of those
liar-for hire types.

154
00:05:34.965 --> 00:05:37.205
That's the part that worries me.

155
00:05:37.206 --> 00:05:40.412
In my past experience.
Reva's always been credible.

156
00:05:40.413 --> 00:05:41.481
Warner? Reva Warner?

157
00:05:41.482 --> 00:05:42.654
You know her?

158
00:05:42.655 --> 00:05:44.136
Yeah we were in the same
graduating year at university.

159
00:05:44.137 --> 00:05:46.171
She and I were always neck-
in-neck for top of the class.

160
00:05:46.172 --> 00:05:48.240
Why does that name
sound so familiar to me?

161
00:05:48.241 --> 00:05:49.654
She's the best-selling
true crime author.

162
00:05:49.655 --> 00:05:50.757
She does those-

163
00:05:50.758 --> 00:05:52.723
Forensic Scientist Debunks
Hollywood Movies videos-

164
00:05:52.724 --> 00:05:53.379
<i>on Youtube.</i>

165
00:05:53.380 --> 00:05:54.619
[Rex groans]

166
00:05:54.620 --> 00:05:55.964
It's pretty tacky.

167
00:05:55.965 --> 00:05:58.930
I mean a good scientist maybe.

168
00:05:58.931 --> 00:06:01.724
But she's just always
been a real spotlight hog.

169
00:06:04.206 --> 00:06:04.896
Okay.

170
00:06:05.137 --> 00:06:05.965
Cancel your weekend plans.

171
00:06:05.966 --> 00:06:07.379
<i>We're taking the case.</i>

172
00:06:08.758 --> 00:06:09.964
With a possible ID on the body-

173
00:06:09.965 --> 00:06:11.896
we have an obligation
to investigate this.

174
00:06:12.965 --> 00:06:13.965
Sarah.

175
00:06:14.068 --> 00:06:15.516
I'm sure you did
your due diligence.

176
00:06:15.517 --> 00:06:16.413
But still.

177
00:06:16.414 --> 00:06:17.585
No. it's okay.

178
00:06:17.586 --> 00:06:20.965
I just have to figure
out how I missed this.

179
00:06:22.586 --> 00:06:23.379
[Sarah sighs]

180
00:06:23.380 --> 00:06:24.413
[Rex whines]

181
00:06:30.103 --> 00:06:31.654
Superintendent Lewis.

182
00:06:31.655 --> 00:06:32.655
Thanks for meeting me.

183
00:06:32.656 --> 00:06:34.448
The pleasure's all mine.

184
00:06:35.344 --> 00:06:36.619
You know. this
David Gallo thing-

185
00:06:36.620 --> 00:06:38.688
is really throwing a
spanner in the works.

186
00:06:38.689 --> 00:06:39.379
Yeah.

187
00:06:39.379 --> 00:06:40.241
Yeah. sure is.

188
00:06:40.242 --> 00:06:41.447
<i>I'm sure we can
still get Powell-</i>

189
00:06:41.448 --> 00:06:44.205
if we put our heads together.

190
00:06:44.206 --> 00:06:45.310
I'm glad you agree.

191
00:06:45.965 --> 00:06:47.205
Which is why I need your team-

192
00:06:47.206 --> 00:06:49.931
to send the case files to Major
Crimes as soon as possible.

193
00:06:51.379 --> 00:06:54.412
It'd be a lot easier if your
team came to Financial Crimes.

194
00:06:54.413 --> 00:06:56.205
<i>My team's already briefed.</i>

195
00:06:56.206 --> 00:06:57.964
Well your team did
all they could.

196
00:06:57.965 --> 00:06:59.516
And a great job at that.

197
00:06:59.517 --> 00:07:00.792
But you know-

198
00:07:00.793 --> 00:07:02.481
the Crown Prosecutor's
just asked Major Crimes-

199
00:07:02.482 --> 00:07:04.000
to take this across
the finish line.

200
00:07:06.172 --> 00:07:08.516
I see what you're doing here.

201
00:07:08.517 --> 00:07:09.965
And it's not going to work.

202
00:07:11.620 --> 00:07:12.724
This is time sensitive.

203
00:07:13.896 --> 00:07:15.240
This is so Major Crimes
is better equipped-

204
00:07:15.241 --> 00:07:16.654
to deal with an
arson investigation.

205
00:07:16.655 --> 00:07:17.482
This-

206
00:07:17.483 --> 00:07:18.862
<i>It's not personal.</i>

207
00:07:19.448 --> 00:07:20.619
Of course.

208
00:07:20.620 --> 00:07:21.965
Purely professional.

209
00:07:23.241 --> 00:07:24.931
I'll have my boys
bring over the files.

210
00:07:25.689 --> 00:07:26.689
Best of luck.

211
00:07:32.310 --> 00:07:33.343
David Gallo.

212
00:07:33.344 --> 00:07:35.481
He spent five years
in Her Majesty's Pen-

213
00:07:35.482 --> 00:07:37.171
for burning down a
heritage building downtown.

214
00:07:37.172 --> 00:07:39.033
Yeah. I remember that case.

215
00:07:39.034 --> 00:07:40.550
A developer wanted
the land cleared-

216
00:07:40.551 --> 00:07:41.826
and couldn't tear
it down legally.

217
00:07:41.827 --> 00:07:43.309
Sarah: <i>I've got the Marshall's
report from that fire.</i>

218
00:07:43.310 --> 00:07:45.343
It's the same MO.

219
00:07:45.344 --> 00:07:47.274
Another aluminum
shaving accelerant bomb.

220
00:07:47.275 --> 00:07:49.481
How did we not catch
that connection before?

221
00:07:49.482 --> 00:07:52.309
Well David's name never turned
up in the initial investigation-

222
00:07:52.310 --> 00:07:53.930
<i>because all signs
pointed to Gene.</i>

223
00:07:53.931 --> 00:07:54.999
And a warrant for his arrest-

224
00:07:55.000 --> 00:07:56.102
only came out
earlier this month-

225
00:07:56.103 --> 00:07:57.861
when he failed to check
in to his parole office.

226
00:07:57.862 --> 00:07:59.619
<i>Ma'am.</i>

227
00:07:59.620 --> 00:08:01.000
Excuse me. what are those?

228
00:08:01.758 --> 00:08:03.172
Those aren't digitized.

229
00:08:06.689 --> 00:08:08.688
Do you have any idea how
long these are going to take-

230
00:08:08.689 --> 00:08:09.689
to sift through?

231
00:08:10.413 --> 00:08:11.999
I take it Superintendent
Lewis wasn't happy-

232
00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:13.102
we were taking over her case?

233
00:08:13.103 --> 00:08:14.792
I think this is
her idea of a joke.

234
00:08:14.793 --> 00:08:16.448
What are we looking
for in here anyway?

235
00:08:17.482 --> 00:08:20.102
Anything that proves that Gene
paid David to set that fire.

236
00:08:20.103 --> 00:08:21.516
Strange cash flow.

237
00:08:21.517 --> 00:08:22.517
Employment records.

238
00:08:22.827 --> 00:08:24.000
Anything. Jesse.

239
00:08:24.586 --> 00:08:25.586
Anything?

240
00:08:27.137 --> 00:08:29.723
Yeah. I do not envy
your day today.

241
00:08:29.724 --> 00:08:31.343
You're not helping?

242
00:08:31.344 --> 00:08:32.412
Uh. wish we could.

243
00:08:32.413 --> 00:08:35.827
But Rex and I have a date
with a parole officer.

244
00:08:37.137 --> 00:08:38.413
<i>Rex. come on pal.</i>

245
00:08:40.068 --> 00:08:41.619
Can you bring me
something caffeinated-

246
00:08:41.620 --> 00:08:42.620
on your way back please?

247
00:08:44.034 --> 00:08:45.034
[ship horn blowing]

248
00:08:46.793 --> 00:08:49.068
[car engine roaring]

249
00:09:00.068 --> 00:09:01.792
Hello cutie.

250
00:09:01.793 --> 00:09:03.585
<i>You don't look like
you're checking in.</i>

251
00:09:03.586 --> 00:09:05.447
<i>Officer Lyddon?</i>

252
00:09:05.448 --> 00:09:06.241
Detective Hudson.

253
00:09:06.241 --> 00:09:07.103
This is my partner Rex.

254
00:09:07.104 --> 00:09:09.585
We're here about David Gallo.

255
00:09:09.586 --> 00:09:11.067
Oh. you mean the son of a bitch-

256
00:09:11.068 --> 00:09:12.481
who got me on the Wall of Shame?

257
00:09:12.482 --> 00:09:13.482
Wall of Shame?

258
00:09:15.551 --> 00:09:16.826
<i>He was the first parolee-</i>

259
00:09:16.827 --> 00:09:18.586
to slip through my fingers.

260
00:09:20.344 --> 00:09:22.068
Guess he turned up somewhere?

261
00:09:22.896 --> 00:09:23.964
Unfortunately. yes.

262
00:09:23.965 --> 00:09:25.964
His body was
identified in a fire.

263
00:09:25.965 --> 00:09:27.343
<i>Do you know if he had-</i>

264
00:09:27.344 --> 00:09:29.551
any associations
with Gene Powell?

265
00:09:30.689 --> 00:09:32.620
Or maybe with the
nightclub Tropiks?

266
00:09:33.137 --> 00:09:34.137
Not that I know of.

267
00:09:35.172 --> 00:09:37.240
Drinking was against
the terms of his parole.

268
00:09:37.241 --> 00:09:38.757
<i>Well it is possible-</i>

269
00:09:38.758 --> 00:09:40.792
that he slipped back into arson.

270
00:09:40.793 --> 00:09:45.792
<i>Was there any indication of
that in your last check-in?</i>

271
00:09:45.793 --> 00:09:47.482
He'd be spitting in
my face if he did.

272
00:09:48.379 --> 00:09:50.103
I helped him get a
job at an auto shop.

273
00:09:50.896 --> 00:09:52.309
Even moved him out
of the halfway house-

274
00:09:52.310 --> 00:09:53.310
into his own place.

275
00:09:54.862 --> 00:09:56.654
I'm going to need his address.

276
00:09:56.655 --> 00:09:57.965
[horn honking]

277
00:09:58.758 --> 00:10:00.275
[indistinct chatter]

278
00:10:00.379 --> 00:10:02.723
♪
[soft pop music]

279
00:10:02.724 --> 00:10:04.240
God. what has it been?

280
00:10:04.241 --> 00:10:04.931
Ten years?

281
00:10:04.932 --> 00:10:06.103
Just about!

282
00:10:07.103 --> 00:10:09.310
You've done very well
for yourself since then.

283
00:10:09.689 --> 00:10:10.826
All luck.

284
00:10:10.827 --> 00:10:12.792
If I hadn't landed
that internship-

285
00:10:12.793 --> 00:10:15.172
at Sutherland Schmidt
right after graduation-

286
00:10:16.965 --> 00:10:18.585
You were up for the same job.

287
00:10:18.586 --> 00:10:19.758
Weren't you?

288
00:10:20.517 --> 00:10:22.067
I mean it's so long ago now.

289
00:10:22.068 --> 00:10:23.862
I'm not sure.

290
00:10:24.965 --> 00:10:26.033
Well who knows?

291
00:10:26.034 --> 00:10:27.585
If things had gone differently-

292
00:10:27.586 --> 00:10:29.481
maybe you'd be the
one meeting me-

293
00:10:29.482 --> 00:10:31.379
at some outpost city like this.

294
00:10:32.413 --> 00:10:35.240
Well. St. John's
is not Toronto.

295
00:10:35.241 --> 00:10:37.482
But it's certainly no outpost.

296
00:10:38.068 --> 00:10:40.067
But your facilities
can't be great here.

297
00:10:40.068 --> 00:10:41.516
How do you mean?

298
00:10:41.517 --> 00:10:43.067
Well with better equipment-

299
00:10:43.068 --> 00:10:46.137
maybe you would've pulled some
workable DNA off that body.

300
00:10:47.206 --> 00:10:50.723
You know. that's actually
what I wanted to talk about.

301
00:10:50.724 --> 00:10:51.724
Um-

302
00:10:52.931 --> 00:10:55.895
I don't understand how you
were able to pull an ID.

303
00:10:55.896 --> 00:10:58.550
<i>Those bones were fully calcined.</i>

304
00:10:58.551 --> 00:11:02.205
Well. when you have
tissue that damaged-

305
00:11:02.206 --> 00:11:02.862
the only solution-

306
00:11:02.863 --> 00:11:05.171
<i>is mitochondrial testing.</i>

307
00:11:05.172 --> 00:11:07.136
We were in the same
Forensics 402 class.

308
00:11:07.137 --> 00:11:08.412
Thank you.

309
00:11:08.413 --> 00:11:13.000
It's just that results from my
test were totally inconclusive.

310
00:11:14.551 --> 00:11:17.136
It must be hard to do
your best work here.

311
00:11:17.137 --> 00:11:19.309
Cops and lawyers always
breathing down your neck-

312
00:11:19.310 --> 00:11:20.655
for a conviction.

313
00:11:22.827 --> 00:11:24.724
Convictions don't
drive my forensics.

314
00:11:25.448 --> 00:11:27.723
The evidence I collect
drives the theory.

315
00:11:27.724 --> 00:11:29.896
Not the other way around.

316
00:11:31.241 --> 00:11:34.585
Actually. I heard a dog runs
the investigations in this town.

317
00:11:34.586 --> 00:11:36.103
<i>I mean is that true?</i>

318
00:11:37.275 --> 00:11:38.275
<i>No.</i>

319
00:11:39.103 --> 00:11:40.999
No. Rex is a part
of the team. yes.

320
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:42.102
But he's a highly trained-

321
00:11:42.103 --> 00:11:42.827
Sarah.

322
00:11:42.828 --> 00:11:44.343
Listen to yourself.

323
00:11:44.344 --> 00:11:45.378
Picking up after a dog.

324
00:11:45.379 --> 00:11:46.862
It is beneath you.

325
00:11:47.655 --> 00:11:48.688
<i>God-what do you use?</i>

326
00:11:48.689 --> 00:11:51.205
<i>Doggie bags to
collect your evidence?</i>

327
00:11:51.206 --> 00:11:53.137
Just tell me how you
got those results. Reva.

328
00:11:54.827 --> 00:11:56.999
It's not complicated.

329
00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:59.171
I tested what they gave me.

330
00:11:59.172 --> 00:12:01.240
The science speaks for itself-

331
00:12:01.241 --> 00:12:02.310
if you're thorough.

332
00:12:03.344 --> 00:12:06.241
♪
[dramatic percussion]

333
00:12:10.448 --> 00:12:12.137
♪
[suspenseful music]

334
00:12:19.137 --> 00:12:19.758
Charlie: <i>Good morning.</i>

335
00:12:19.758 --> 00:12:20.758
Good morning. Charlie.

336
00:12:21.310 --> 00:12:22.310
Sarah.

337
00:12:22.862 --> 00:12:24.142
I thought you
could use a coffee.

338
00:12:24.517 --> 00:12:25.517
What is all-?

339
00:12:26.344 --> 00:12:27.344
Or you canhave it.

340
00:12:27.862 --> 00:12:28.793
What is all this?

341
00:12:28.794 --> 00:12:30.826
I've pulled exhibits
from the courthouse.

342
00:12:30.827 --> 00:12:32.550
We're testing the remains again.

343
00:12:32.551 --> 00:12:35.654
Does this mean that
you believe Reva now?

344
00:12:35.655 --> 00:12:37.171
It means it's possible.

345
00:12:37.172 --> 00:12:38.999
So we're going to try to
replicate her results.

346
00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:40.240
Retesting a hypothesis-

347
00:12:40.241 --> 00:12:42.688
is a crucial part of the
scientific method. after all.

348
00:12:42.689 --> 00:12:43.723
Did Reva get into your head-

349
00:12:43.724 --> 00:12:44.413
last night?

350
00:12:44.414 --> 00:12:45.896
Absolutely not.

351
00:12:46.896 --> 00:12:48.482
♪
[mysterious music]

352
00:12:49.793 --> 00:12:50.793
[Rex barks]

353
00:12:54.137 --> 00:12:54.862
[Rex barks]

354
00:12:54.965 --> 00:12:55.965
[Rex sniffing]

355
00:12:55.965 --> 00:12:56.965
What is it pal?

356
00:12:58.586 --> 00:12:59.448
[Rex barking]

357
00:12:59.449 --> 00:13:00.689
What?

358
00:13:01.689 --> 00:13:02.723
[Rex whines]

359
00:13:02.724 --> 00:13:04.999
[Rex barking]

360
00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:06.999
Sarah: <i>It should just
be metal fragments-</i>

361
00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.172
<i>collected from the fire.</i>

362
00:13:16.896 --> 00:13:18.895
<i>Charlie: Looks like some
kind of circuit board?</i>

363
00:13:18.896 --> 00:13:19.930
I'll take it down to Jesse.

364
00:13:19.931 --> 00:13:20.964
See what he comes up with.

365
00:13:20.965 --> 00:13:21.965
Okay.

366
00:13:23.379 --> 00:13:24.482
<i>Nice work Rex.</i>

367
00:13:33.034 --> 00:13:34.447
Are you okay?

368
00:13:34.448 --> 00:13:36.033
Yeah. I'm just um-

369
00:13:36.034 --> 00:13:36.862
[clears throat]

370
00:13:36.863 --> 00:13:39.412
having a tough
week. or something.

371
00:13:39.413 --> 00:13:40.724
Science isn't fickle.

372
00:13:41.137 --> 00:13:42.792
If there's something that
we missed in all of this-

373
00:13:42.793 --> 00:13:44.000
we'll find it now.

374
00:13:47.034 --> 00:13:48.034
I hope so.

375
00:13:49.758 --> 00:13:50.758
[door lock beeps]

376
00:13:56.862 --> 00:13:57.862
Jesse.

377
00:13:58.758 --> 00:13:59.379
[Rex whines]

378
00:13:59.379 --> 00:14:00.379
Yeah.

379
00:14:00.689 --> 00:14:01.344
<i>Whoa.</i>

380
00:14:01.344 --> 00:14:02.172
<i>You doing all right?</i>

381
00:14:02.172 --> 00:14:03.172
I have been-

382
00:14:03.173 --> 00:14:05.792
<i>drowning in spreadsheets
for several hours.</i>

383
00:14:05.793 --> 00:14:07.827
Charlie: <i>Any idea
what those are?</i>

384
00:14:09.344 --> 00:14:10.619
Jesse: <i>Huh.</i>

385
00:14:10.620 --> 00:14:11.620
These are in bad shape.

386
00:14:11.620 --> 00:14:12.620
<i>But-</i>

387
00:14:13.344 --> 00:14:15.516
they look like super-
conductor chips.

388
00:14:15.517 --> 00:14:17.240
You want to explain
that to the rest of us-

389
00:14:17.241 --> 00:14:18.274
who don't crack
open our cellphones-

390
00:14:18.275 --> 00:14:18.931
<i>for fun?</i>

391
00:14:18.931 --> 00:14:19.793
I did that one time.

392
00:14:19.794 --> 00:14:20.914
And it was very educational.

393
00:14:21.379 --> 00:14:22.275
These are in everything.

394
00:14:22.276 --> 00:14:24.171
Cellphones. minivans.

395
00:14:24.172 --> 00:14:25.034
Gaming consoles.

396
00:14:25.035 --> 00:14:26.654
Anything with computing powers.

397
00:14:26.655 --> 00:14:27.655
Are they valuable?

398
00:14:28.137 --> 00:14:29.619
Oh. they're worth
their weight in gold.

399
00:14:29.620 --> 00:14:31.300
I mean there's a global
shortage right now.

400
00:14:32.448 --> 00:14:34.343
What is a nightclub
owner doing with them?

401
00:14:34.344 --> 00:14:36.378
Do you have any transactions
that would explain-

402
00:14:36.379 --> 00:14:38.033
how Gene could've gotten
his hands on those?

403
00:14:38.034 --> 00:14:39.240
Jesse: <i>No. here's the thing.</i>

404
00:14:39.241 --> 00:14:41.240
I went through Financial
Crimes files on Gene.

405
00:14:41.241 --> 00:14:43.067
And I just can't make
sense of any of it.

406
00:14:43.068 --> 00:14:44.930
I have trouble with
Excel spreadsheets too.

407
00:14:44.931 --> 00:14:45.999
Jesse: <i>Not that.</i>

408
00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:47.067
<i>For one-</i>

409
00:14:47.068 --> 00:14:48.930
this guy has more money
coming in than going out.

410
00:14:48.931 --> 00:14:49.758
Okay?

411
00:14:49.759 --> 00:14:51.378
There's no sign
of any withdrawal-

412
00:14:51.379 --> 00:14:52.447
to pay David the arsonist-

413
00:14:52.448 --> 00:14:54.619
or to even buy tech like this.

414
00:14:54.620 --> 00:14:56.171
So maybe he's got a
second source of income?

415
00:14:56.172 --> 00:14:57.378
Jesse: <i>That's what
I was thinking too.</i>

416
00:14:57.379 --> 00:14:58.896
<i>But this is where
things get weird.</i>

417
00:14:59.482 --> 00:15:00.619
<i>It's like Financial Crimes-</i>

418
00:15:00.620 --> 00:15:02.688
<i>is running six different
investigations on this guy.</i>

419
00:15:02.689 --> 00:15:03.999
There are files
on cases in here-

420
00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:06.481
that already laid
convictions on other people.

421
00:15:06.482 --> 00:15:07.793
Who's this guy?

422
00:15:07.896 --> 00:15:09.205
Jesse: <i>A known gun smuggler.</i>

423
00:15:09.206 --> 00:15:12.309
There are files on a bunch of
other dealers that were nabbed.

424
00:15:12.310 --> 00:15:14.481
So the Tropiks is
a criminal hotspot?

425
00:15:14.482 --> 00:15:15.826
Well they didn't
include a guide-

426
00:15:15.827 --> 00:15:17.205
on how to connect
any of these files.

427
00:15:17.206 --> 00:15:19.274
I don't know how Gene
is mixed up in all this.

428
00:15:19.275 --> 00:15:20.481
Donovan: <i>You know what?</i>

429
00:15:20.482 --> 00:15:22.861
Let me have another conversation
with Superintendent Lewis.

430
00:15:22.862 --> 00:15:24.895
And we'll get the answer
directly from the source.

431
00:15:24.896 --> 00:15:25.896
[elevator pings]

432
00:15:29.586 --> 00:15:30.482
Hey!

433
00:15:30.482 --> 00:15:31.275
There you are.

434
00:15:31.276 --> 00:15:32.619
I was just coming to see you.

435
00:15:32.620 --> 00:15:34.033
Solved it already?

436
00:15:34.034 --> 00:15:35.102
Must be a record.

437
00:15:35.103 --> 00:15:36.274
Pretty impressive.

438
00:15:36.275 --> 00:15:37.343
Yeah that's very funny.

439
00:15:37.344 --> 00:15:38.275
[Lewis chuckles]

440
00:15:38.276 --> 00:15:39.964
You know. almost as
funny as sending us-

441
00:15:39.965 --> 00:15:42.619
an entire recycling
plant's worth of paper.

442
00:15:42.620 --> 00:15:44.274
We can't make heads
or tails of it.

443
00:15:44.275 --> 00:15:45.550
Well you should
have known better.

444
00:15:45.551 --> 00:15:48.343
Trying to cram a year's worth
of investigation into a weekend?

445
00:15:48.344 --> 00:15:49.034
Ha.

446
00:15:49.034 --> 00:15:49.689
Come on now.

447
00:15:49.689 --> 00:15:50.379
Wait.

448
00:15:50.379 --> 00:15:51.379
Hold on. a year's worth?

449
00:15:52.551 --> 00:15:54.240
This is about way
more than just a fire.

450
00:15:54.241 --> 00:15:55.964
What else are you
trying to nab Gene for?

451
00:15:55.965 --> 00:15:57.412
It's your investigation now.

452
00:15:57.413 --> 00:15:58.895
<i>Figure it out.</i>

453
00:15:58.896 --> 00:16:00.861
Vanessa. I don't
know what I've done-

454
00:16:00.862 --> 00:16:02.826
to warrant this
kind of hostility.

455
00:16:02.827 --> 00:16:04.102
Just can't we work
together here?

456
00:16:04.103 --> 00:16:05.103
<i>You've had your chance.</i>

457
00:16:05.758 --> 00:16:07.826
But Major Crimes needs
their win. right?

458
00:16:07.827 --> 00:16:09.378
My team just what-?

459
00:16:09.379 --> 00:16:10.550
Gets sidelined?

460
00:16:10.551 --> 00:16:12.964
All your team's work is
going to go for naught-

461
00:16:12.965 --> 00:16:14.757
if we can't crack this.

462
00:16:14.758 --> 00:16:16.136
We just need to know-

463
00:16:16.137 --> 00:16:18.067
how David Gallo factors in.

464
00:16:18.068 --> 00:16:19.688
<i>Talk to somebody who knows.</i>

465
00:16:19.689 --> 00:16:21.655
I've given you all I got.

466
00:16:23.758 --> 00:16:25.172
[Donovan sighs]

467
00:16:27.793 --> 00:16:28.689
This is David's place.

468
00:16:28.690 --> 00:16:29.964
<i>Uh-uh.</i>

469
00:16:29.965 --> 00:16:31.551
<i>This building has
a no pets policy.</i>

470
00:16:32.965 --> 00:16:33.620
[Rex barks]

471
00:16:33.621 --> 00:16:34.964
Good think he's not a pet.

472
00:16:34.965 --> 00:16:35.965
[Rex growls]

473
00:16:36.275 --> 00:16:37.275
<i>What the-?</i>

474
00:16:38.000 --> 00:16:39.999
<i>Your tenant has been
dead for two months.</i>

475
00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:41.378
<i>You didn't notice
he wasn't here?</i>

476
00:16:41.379 --> 00:16:42.895
<i>Dead. alive.</i>

477
00:16:42.896 --> 00:16:43.964
[Rex sniffing]

478
00:16:43.965 --> 00:16:45.605
<i>I don't care so long
so the rent comes in.</i>

479
00:16:46.551 --> 00:16:47.551
[Rex barks]

480
00:16:47.552 --> 00:16:49.551
Looks like David didn't
get the no pet memo.

481
00:16:51.448 --> 00:16:52.448
Hmm.

482
00:16:53.344 --> 00:16:55.378
Who's been feeding the fish?

483
00:16:55.379 --> 00:16:56.826
I live off-property.

484
00:16:56.827 --> 00:16:57.827
Couldn't tell you.

485
00:17:04.310 --> 00:17:05.310
Someone's expecting.

486
00:17:06.965 --> 00:17:08.689
♪
[mysterious music]

487
00:17:15.896 --> 00:17:18.172
[Rex sniffing]

488
00:17:18.275 --> 00:17:20.689
[Rex barking]

489
00:17:21.896 --> 00:17:22.896
What've you got. pal?

490
00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:26.000
[Rex barking]

491
00:17:35.172 --> 00:17:36.689
♪
[suspenseful music]

492
00:17:40.413 --> 00:17:41.413
[knocking on window]

493
00:17:43.172 --> 00:17:44.861
Charlie: <i>I've got
good news or bad news-</i>

494
00:17:44.862 --> 00:17:46.137
<i>depending on how your day went.</i>

495
00:17:52.310 --> 00:17:53.241
Aluminum shavings.

496
00:17:53.242 --> 00:17:54.274
<i>Looks like it could be a match</i>-

497
00:17:54.275 --> 00:17:54.965
<i>to the accelerant bomb.</i>

498
00:17:54.966 --> 00:17:56.655
But I'll have to test it.

499
00:17:57.172 --> 00:17:58.137
You found these where?

500
00:17:58.138 --> 00:17:59.999
In David's apartment.

501
00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:01.654
<i>Looks like he is a part of this.</i>

502
00:18:01.655 --> 00:18:03.689
Reva may have been right.

503
00:18:04.724 --> 00:18:06.084
Karma: <i>Well. we
can't say the same.</i>

504
00:18:07.448 --> 00:18:09.688
Sarah and I each conducted
the DNA testing again.

505
00:18:09.689 --> 00:18:10.448
And results-

506
00:18:10.449 --> 00:18:12.413
are still inconclusive.

507
00:18:12.517 --> 00:18:13.379
Sorry.

508
00:18:13.379 --> 00:18:14.103
Sarah: <i>No.</i>

509
00:18:14.104 --> 00:18:15.447
No. it's not that we failed.

510
00:18:15.448 --> 00:18:16.689
It's literally impossible.

511
00:18:17.931 --> 00:18:18.620
There's no conceivable way-

512
00:18:18.621 --> 00:18:20.240
that Reva pulled David's DNA.

513
00:18:20.241 --> 00:18:22.274
But she presented a DNA match.

514
00:18:22.275 --> 00:18:23.654
How is that possible?

515
00:18:23.655 --> 00:18:24.895
Sarah: <i>Well-</i>

516
00:18:24.896 --> 00:18:27.136
the Defense was ready to spring
David on us at the trial.

517
00:18:28.206 --> 00:18:30.862
I wonder if Reva
lied under oath.

518
00:18:35.517 --> 00:18:38.000
I hope you didn't call us down
here to intimidate my client.

519
00:18:38.793 --> 00:18:40.073
Charlie: <i>No I can
assure you not.</i>

520
00:18:41.793 --> 00:18:42.861
From what emerged in court-

521
00:18:42.862 --> 00:18:45.378
we are now officially
looking into David Gallo.

522
00:18:45.379 --> 00:18:46.964
<i>Any idea why-</i>

523
00:18:46.965 --> 00:18:48.405
he might have targeted
your business?

524
00:18:50.551 --> 00:18:52.688
Well he used to be a regular-

525
00:18:52.689 --> 00:18:53.655
before prison-

526
00:18:53.655 --> 00:18:54.551
<i>did a number on him.</i>

527
00:18:54.551 --> 00:18:55.551
What do you mean?

528
00:18:55.965 --> 00:18:58.102
He had a short fuse.

529
00:18:58.103 --> 00:18:59.895
Started picking fights.

530
00:18:59.896 --> 00:19:03.585
We had to ban him two
weeks before the fire.

531
00:19:03.586 --> 00:19:05.447
That's why he torched the place?

532
00:19:05.448 --> 00:19:06.448
Well-

533
00:19:06.449 --> 00:19:08.275
It's not easy being
kicked out of paradise.

534
00:19:11.793 --> 00:19:12.895
Yeah. um-

535
00:19:12.896 --> 00:19:16.550
this was taken two
days before the fire.

536
00:19:16.551 --> 00:19:18.136
That's David Gallo. right?

537
00:19:18.137 --> 00:19:19.481
Detective Hudson. careful.

538
00:19:19.482 --> 00:19:21.067
We don't have to be here.

539
00:19:21.068 --> 00:19:23.586
Just trying to establish a
timeline for our suspect.

540
00:19:24.344 --> 00:19:26.172
Security must have
been lax that night.

541
00:19:27.344 --> 00:19:28.665
Maybe he was scoping
out the place.

542
00:19:28.689 --> 00:19:30.793
Except those are the
<i>Employees Only</i> stairs.

543
00:19:32.172 --> 00:19:33.332
We checked on the floor plan.

544
00:19:33.862 --> 00:19:34.655
It's the same place-

545
00:19:34.656 --> 00:19:36.343
where Kieran
McCall. arms dealer-

546
00:19:36.344 --> 00:19:37.586
<i>once headed.</i>

547
00:19:37.689 --> 00:19:39.274
A corrupt port authority.

548
00:19:39.275 --> 00:19:40.137
<i>Oh and-</i>

549
00:19:40.138 --> 00:19:41.585
<i>a contraband tobacco smuggler.</i>

550
00:19:41.586 --> 00:19:42.413
Alright. Hudson.

551
00:19:42.414 --> 00:19:43.619
I don't like where
this is headed.

552
00:19:43.620 --> 00:19:45.861
Doesn't feel like Gallo should
be going up those stairs-

553
00:19:45.862 --> 00:19:46.895
unless he was on the payroll.

554
00:19:46.896 --> 00:19:47.896
Does it?

555
00:19:49.000 --> 00:19:50.080
If you really believe that-

556
00:19:51.206 --> 00:19:52.516
good luck proving it.

557
00:19:52.517 --> 00:19:53.793
We'll see you on Monday.

558
00:19:54.310 --> 00:19:56.930
It's just not possible Reva
came to that conclusion-

559
00:19:56.931 --> 00:19:57.965
with her methodology.

560
00:19:59.551 --> 00:20:02.447
I think she was led to that
conclusion by the defense.

561
00:20:02.448 --> 00:20:03.999
Charlie: <i>Which means
they were counting on us-</i>

562
00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:06.067
not being able to connect
Gallo to this fire.

563
00:20:06.068 --> 00:20:08.388
They had a ready-made scapegoat
prepared to throw the case.

564
00:20:08.724 --> 00:20:10.240
That seems far-fetched.

565
00:20:10.241 --> 00:20:11.412
[Rex barks]

566
00:20:11.413 --> 00:20:12.964
Uh-don't say fetch.

567
00:20:12.965 --> 00:20:14.171
Can you prove any of this?

568
00:20:14.172 --> 00:20:15.585
Or is it just a hunch?

569
00:20:15.586 --> 00:20:16.655
No it is not a hunch.

570
00:20:16.931 --> 00:20:18.136
It's a theory.

571
00:20:18.137 --> 00:20:19.274
Michael: <i>So you expect me-</i>

572
00:20:19.275 --> 00:20:20.206
to walk into court tomorrow-

573
00:20:20.207 --> 00:20:22.309
crying collusion and
falsifying evidence?

574
00:20:22.310 --> 00:20:24.309
With nothing to back it up?

575
00:20:24.310 --> 00:20:25.447
We are going to prove it.

576
00:20:25.448 --> 00:20:26.448
Just give us time.

577
00:20:27.689 --> 00:20:29.379
24 hours is all
the time we have.

578
00:20:32.655 --> 00:20:33.895
Sorry.

579
00:20:33.896 --> 00:20:35.309
So how are we going to prove it?

580
00:20:35.310 --> 00:20:37.412
There's no paper trail
between David and Gene.

581
00:20:37.413 --> 00:20:38.654
Maybe we don't have to find one.

582
00:20:38.655 --> 00:20:40.550
If we can prove Reva
falsified evidence-

583
00:20:40.551 --> 00:20:42.585
then the case falls apart right?

584
00:20:42.586 --> 00:20:45.136
Uh-leave that with me.

585
00:20:45.137 --> 00:20:46.550
It's a big if Sarah.

586
00:20:46.551 --> 00:20:47.413
We need to attack this-

587
00:20:47.414 --> 00:20:48.723
from every angle.

588
00:20:48.724 --> 00:20:50.447
What if we can find
someone in David's life-

589
00:20:50.448 --> 00:20:53.205
who can speak to
their relationship?

590
00:20:53.206 --> 00:20:54.309
I called the hospital-

591
00:20:54.310 --> 00:20:55.999
that performed that
ultrasound you found. Charlie.

592
00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:58.793
Here's the list of all the women
who had appointments that day.

593
00:21:00.137 --> 00:21:02.482
I know exactly who
we're looking for.

594
00:21:12.620 --> 00:21:14.620
I think we have
something of yours.

595
00:21:17.862 --> 00:21:20.620
♪
[dramatic percussion]

596
00:21:26.482 --> 00:21:28.481
Amanda.

597
00:21:28.482 --> 00:21:30.655
What was this doing
at David's apartment?

598
00:21:33.103 --> 00:21:35.723
David asked to see the sonogram.

599
00:21:35.724 --> 00:21:37.793
We became pretty close
over his probation.

600
00:21:37.896 --> 00:21:39.481
I'd say you became
more than close.

601
00:21:39.482 --> 00:21:40.585
<i>He would have been-</i>

602
00:21:40.586 --> 00:21:43.792
the first person to see this.

603
00:21:43.793 --> 00:21:45.033
He had a check-in with you-

604
00:21:45.034 --> 00:21:46.861
a half an hour after
this appointment.

605
00:21:46.862 --> 00:21:47.827
David's the father.

606
00:21:47.828 --> 00:21:49.000
Isn't he?

607
00:21:50.620 --> 00:21:52.275
[Rex whines]

608
00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:56.550
When David got out. no
one believed in him.

609
00:21:56.551 --> 00:21:57.654
♪
[soft music]

610
00:21:57.655 --> 00:22:01.067
Everyone here was just
waiting for him to reoffend.

611
00:22:01.068 --> 00:22:04.034
There was something tender in
him if you looked a bit deeper.

612
00:22:06.344 --> 00:22:07.584
<i>It's clear you cared about him.</i>

613
00:22:09.758 --> 00:22:12.378
That's why I need you to
be honest with me now.

614
00:22:12.379 --> 00:22:14.757
<i>What else are you hiding?</i>

615
00:22:14.758 --> 00:22:17.033
The day of the ultrasound-

616
00:22:17.034 --> 00:22:19.655
he told me he was worried
about providing for us.

617
00:22:21.137 --> 00:22:22.827
And he told me he had a job.

618
00:22:24.137 --> 00:22:25.688
The Tropiks fire?

619
00:22:25.689 --> 00:22:27.378
I didn't care to
hear the details.

620
00:22:27.379 --> 00:22:29.102
But I told him that if
he did anything stupid-

621
00:22:29.103 --> 00:22:30.516
he'd be out of our
lives for good.

622
00:22:30.517 --> 00:22:32.378
He may have still taken the job.

623
00:22:32.379 --> 00:22:35.619
We found some material
in his apartment-

624
00:22:35.620 --> 00:22:37.068
that matched the
accelerant bomb.

625
00:22:37.448 --> 00:22:38.448
No.

626
00:22:39.241 --> 00:22:40.343
He told me he'd refused-

627
00:22:40.344 --> 00:22:41.964
<i>to do it.</i>

628
00:22:41.965 --> 00:22:44.310
But that he needed to disappear
for a while to stay safe.

629
00:22:45.034 --> 00:22:46.861
And in the meantime.
you kept the fish fed.

630
00:22:46.862 --> 00:22:50.033
He promised he'd be back in
time for his next check-in.

631
00:22:50.034 --> 00:22:52.448
Even after we filed the
warrant for his arrest-

632
00:22:54.517 --> 00:22:56.379
I was hoping that
he'd come back-

633
00:22:57.551 --> 00:22:58.758
until yesterday.

634
00:23:02.344 --> 00:23:03.413
[Rex grunts]

635
00:23:05.827 --> 00:23:06.862
What is he doing?

636
00:23:07.206 --> 00:23:08.448
[Rex sniffing]

637
00:23:11.655 --> 00:23:12.655
[Rex barks]

638
00:23:14.172 --> 00:23:15.310
He's on to something.

639
00:23:16.482 --> 00:23:17.344
What have you got pal?

640
00:23:17.345 --> 00:23:18.620
[Rex barking]

641
00:23:31.344 --> 00:23:33.758
Of course you found the one
item in this office of his.

642
00:23:38.034 --> 00:23:40.067
He told me to keep
them safe in case-

643
00:23:40.068 --> 00:23:41.413
<i>he need them for insurance.</i>

644
00:23:47.655 --> 00:23:49.999
We have bomb components
at David's house-

645
00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:51.999
and proof that he was
commissioned for a crime-

646
00:23:52.000 --> 00:23:53.241
before the fire.

647
00:23:53.586 --> 00:23:55.723
So why do we not have
everything we need?

648
00:23:55.724 --> 00:23:57.343
We still can't
prove definitively-

649
00:23:57.344 --> 00:23:58.619
that Gene hired him.

650
00:23:58.620 --> 00:24:00.206
I wish it was that simple.

651
00:24:01.344 --> 00:24:03.378
But I think I
believe Amanda too.

652
00:24:03.379 --> 00:24:04.585
Because he didn't
go through with it?

653
00:24:04.586 --> 00:24:06.895
Not after he found out
he had a baby on the way.

654
00:24:06.896 --> 00:24:08.309
Sarah: <i>Wait. okay so-</i>

655
00:24:08.310 --> 00:24:09.378
if we want to believe Reva-

656
00:24:09.379 --> 00:24:11.240
how did he end up in that fire?

657
00:24:11.241 --> 00:24:12.896
I think he might've
been murdered.

658
00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:14.171
[Rex whines]

659
00:24:14.172 --> 00:24:16.102
Because he backed
out of the job?

660
00:24:16.103 --> 00:24:17.550
Or for his silence.

661
00:24:17.551 --> 00:24:20.481
Amanda said that David gave
her these as insurance.

662
00:24:20.482 --> 00:24:22.826
Maybe it was for
leverage against Gene-

663
00:24:22.827 --> 00:24:24.241
for whatever he
was using them for.

664
00:24:24.344 --> 00:24:26.171
That won't hold up
in court Charlie.

665
00:24:26.172 --> 00:24:28.861
Or maybe it was for
Amanda and the baby?

666
00:24:28.862 --> 00:24:30.412
Because if was looking
for a payday. those chips-

667
00:24:30.413 --> 00:24:31.654
could be worth a lot of money.

668
00:24:31.655 --> 00:24:32.861
Charlie: <i>The part that
doesn't make sense-</i>

669
00:24:32.862 --> 00:24:34.067
is why would Jean let them burn?

670
00:24:34.068 --> 00:24:35.586
Jesse: <i>Well-</i>

671
00:24:36.241 --> 00:24:37.241
they're junk.

672
00:24:37.965 --> 00:24:38.689
I'm sorry?

673
00:24:38.690 --> 00:24:40.136
Yeah. I tested dozens of these.

674
00:24:40.137 --> 00:24:41.619
None of them have a current.

675
00:24:41.620 --> 00:24:42.965
They're less than worthless.

676
00:24:44.827 --> 00:24:48.827
Because this was never
about the nightclub.

677
00:24:52.034 --> 00:24:53.551
Gene was stuck with
faulty product.

678
00:24:54.655 --> 00:24:55.964
You think he was
selling contraband?

679
00:24:55.965 --> 00:24:57.102
If he's a contraband merchant-

680
00:24:57.103 --> 00:24:58.551
these numbers would make sense.

681
00:24:59.482 --> 00:25:00.550
Yeah.

682
00:25:00.551 --> 00:25:02.240
Financial Crimes have
all these large deposits-

683
00:25:02.241 --> 00:25:03.274
<i>highlighted on
their spreadsheets.</i>

684
00:25:03.275 --> 00:25:04.689
<i>I didn't know what
they were before.</i>

685
00:25:09.689 --> 00:25:10.999
Sarah: <i>Thank you so much-</i>

686
00:25:11.000 --> 00:25:12.412
for coming.

687
00:25:12.413 --> 00:25:14.240
Oh it's my pleasure!

688
00:25:14.241 --> 00:25:17.792
Though do I have to remind you
that there's a case ongoing?

689
00:25:17.793 --> 00:25:19.861
So I can't help you too much.

690
00:25:19.862 --> 00:25:23.102
Well this is for a separate
investigation on David Gallo.

691
00:25:23.103 --> 00:25:24.688
Getting your statement
would be very helpful-

692
00:25:24.689 --> 00:25:26.655
since my results came up short.

693
00:25:29.413 --> 00:25:31.102
It's big of you to admit
that you were wrong.

694
00:25:31.103 --> 00:25:32.585
<i>I also-</i>

695
00:25:32.586 --> 00:25:35.378
was thinking about what
you said the other night.

696
00:25:35.379 --> 00:25:36.517
About this job being-

697
00:25:37.517 --> 00:25:38.482
you know-

698
00:25:38.483 --> 00:25:39.586
beneath me.

699
00:25:40.241 --> 00:25:43.033
Do you get to travel
for work a lot?

700
00:25:43.034 --> 00:25:44.378
Yeah. someone hires us.

701
00:25:44.379 --> 00:25:45.758
We go consult.

702
00:25:46.379 --> 00:25:47.999
What are you looking
to make a change?

703
00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:50.033
It'd just be an awfully
nice way to see the world.

704
00:25:50.034 --> 00:25:51.585
<i>You didn't-</i>

705
00:25:51.586 --> 00:25:54.378
test the evidence
out in Toronto?

706
00:25:54.379 --> 00:25:55.792
No. I can get access to a lab-

707
00:25:55.793 --> 00:25:57.205
pretty much anywhere
in the world.

708
00:25:57.206 --> 00:25:58.309
<i>It's tricky here though-</i>

709
00:25:58.310 --> 00:25:59.792
<i>with just the one worth using.</i>

710
00:25:59.793 --> 00:26:01.033
Kernwell Research Centre?

711
00:26:01.034 --> 00:26:02.034
No. God no.

712
00:26:02.034 --> 00:26:02.724
AtlanTech Labs.

713
00:26:02.724 --> 00:26:03.724
[elevator pings]

714
00:26:05.448 --> 00:26:06.585
Oh okay.

715
00:26:06.586 --> 00:26:07.930
So this officer will take
you to get your statement.

716
00:26:07.931 --> 00:26:09.000
<i>Great.</i>

717
00:26:10.551 --> 00:26:13.206
And I will keep an
eye out for openings.

718
00:26:16.517 --> 00:26:18.068
♪
[suspenseful music]

719
00:26:23.793 --> 00:26:24.448
Jesse?

720
00:26:24.448 --> 00:26:25.448
It's AtlanTech Labs.

721
00:26:26.206 --> 00:26:27.724
Get me anything you can find.

722
00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:38.103
Clock's ticking.

723
00:26:38.551 --> 00:26:39.620
You get your guy yet?

724
00:26:40.689 --> 00:26:42.413
Vanessa. Major Crimes
is trying to help you.

725
00:26:43.758 --> 00:26:45.930
And it's not going to reflect
well on Financial Crimes either-

726
00:26:45.931 --> 00:26:48.861
if this case falls apart now.

727
00:26:48.862 --> 00:26:51.033
<i>But if you get the win-</i>

728
00:26:51.034 --> 00:26:53.481
I doubt if you'd
share it with us.

729
00:26:53.482 --> 00:26:55.103
That doesn't seem fair. does it?

730
00:26:55.965 --> 00:26:58.378
So let me get this straight.

731
00:26:58.379 --> 00:27:00.516
It's more important
for my team to fail-

732
00:27:00.517 --> 00:27:01.586
than to get Gene Powell?

733
00:27:03.068 --> 00:27:04.861
What exactly is going on here?

734
00:27:04.862 --> 00:27:05.689
<i>Don't play dumb.</i>

735
00:27:05.690 --> 00:27:08.930
The Chief is talking retirement.

736
00:27:08.931 --> 00:27:11.378
So your scooping our case-

737
00:27:11.379 --> 00:27:13.619
is just a move to start
campaigning for the job.

738
00:27:13.620 --> 00:27:15.757
That's news to me.

739
00:27:15.758 --> 00:27:17.447
And what makes you think
I'd even want that job?

740
00:27:17.448 --> 00:27:18.550
Who wouldn't?

741
00:27:18.551 --> 00:27:20.241
Never even crossed my mind.

742
00:27:20.965 --> 00:27:22.034
Mmmm.

743
00:27:24.068 --> 00:27:25.274
The only thing-

744
00:27:25.275 --> 00:27:28.585
<i>that is on my plate right
now is getting Gene Powell.</i>

745
00:27:28.586 --> 00:27:29.793
And I need your help.

746
00:27:31.172 --> 00:27:33.000
Please.

747
00:27:34.206 --> 00:27:35.793
That's all you had to say.

748
00:27:37.758 --> 00:27:39.516
My team has been after
Gene Powell for years.

749
00:27:39.517 --> 00:27:41.550
There was an influx
of contraband in town.

750
00:27:41.551 --> 00:27:43.964
And the merchants seemed to
have only one thing in common.

751
00:27:43.965 --> 00:27:45.033
They went through Tropiks.

752
00:27:45.034 --> 00:27:46.274
Exactly.

753
00:27:46.275 --> 00:27:48.447
Now we couldn't tell how Gene
was involved in the scheme.

754
00:27:48.448 --> 00:27:50.309
But the club was
a hub of activity.

755
00:27:50.310 --> 00:27:52.309
And clearly he was
getting kickbacks.

756
00:27:52.310 --> 00:27:55.102
I mean I couldn't trace any
of these massive deposits.

757
00:27:55.103 --> 00:27:56.136
So he was just a middleman?

758
00:27:56.137 --> 00:27:57.103
Lewis: <i>No.</i>

759
00:27:57.104 --> 00:27:58.999
Not with the kind of
money he had coming in.

760
00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:00.792
I mean that's a healthy cut.

761
00:28:00.793 --> 00:28:05.413
What if he was paid in
advance by the buyer?

762
00:28:05.517 --> 00:28:06.517
But the chips were faulty.

763
00:28:06.518 --> 00:28:07.826
Which-

764
00:28:07.827 --> 00:28:09.757
Which means that he'd be on the
hook for millions to somebody.

765
00:28:09.758 --> 00:28:11.930
Yeah. which is why the
nightclub had to go-

766
00:28:11.931 --> 00:28:13.205
and take the chips with it.

767
00:28:13.206 --> 00:28:15.999
And if David wasn't going
to help with the problem-

768
00:28:16.000 --> 00:28:17.619
maybe he needed to go too.

769
00:28:17.620 --> 00:28:18.964
With fatherhood on the horizon-

770
00:28:18.965 --> 00:28:20.171
he could have been threatening-

771
00:28:20.172 --> 00:28:21.516
to come clean about
all this stuff.

772
00:28:21.517 --> 00:28:22.792
[phone pings]

773
00:28:22.793 --> 00:28:24.034
Yeah. it all makes sense.

774
00:28:24.586 --> 00:28:25.757
How are we going to prove it-

775
00:28:25.758 --> 00:28:27.310
before the trial
resumes tomorrow?

776
00:28:28.482 --> 00:28:29.482
We may not have to.

777
00:28:31.517 --> 00:28:32.517
[Rex barks]

778
00:28:34.275 --> 00:28:35.000
Hey.

779
00:28:35.001 --> 00:28:36.412
You got something for me?

780
00:28:36.413 --> 00:28:37.413
Jesse: <i>Yeah just the CCTV-</i>

781
00:28:37.414 --> 00:28:39.586
from the lab where Reva
was running her tests.

782
00:28:49.413 --> 00:28:50.275
Charlie: <i>Special delivery.</i>

783
00:28:50.275 --> 00:28:51.275
You were right.

784
00:28:51.276 --> 00:28:52.756
That doesn't look
like court evidence.

785
00:28:53.344 --> 00:28:54.447
But that package-

786
00:28:54.448 --> 00:28:57.068
doesn't exactly read David
Gallo's DNA on it either.

787
00:28:58.482 --> 00:29:00.585
It's not enough to prove
our collusion theory.

788
00:29:00.586 --> 00:29:01.826
Yeah but who's
doing the drop off?

789
00:29:01.827 --> 00:29:03.758
That might be of
interest to you.

790
00:29:03.862 --> 00:29:04.862
♪
[suspenseful music]

791
00:29:09.655 --> 00:29:10.793
Sarah: <i>Gene's lawyer.</i>

792
00:29:11.310 --> 00:29:12.550
I need to borrow Rex.

793
00:29:12.551 --> 00:29:13.724
[Rex barks]

794
00:29:15.103 --> 00:29:16.137
♪
[dramatic percussion]

795
00:29:23.103 --> 00:29:24.241
Sarah Truong.

796
00:29:25.034 --> 00:29:26.067
Ten years. no call.

797
00:29:26.068 --> 00:29:27.988
And now I hear from you
three times in a weekend.

798
00:29:29.379 --> 00:29:30.517
And you are-?

799
00:29:30.620 --> 00:29:31.620
Detective Hudson.

800
00:29:31.655 --> 00:29:32.826
<i>And this is my partner.</i>

801
00:29:32.827 --> 00:29:33.724
Rex!

802
00:29:33.724 --> 00:29:34.413
<i>Yes yes!</i>

803
00:29:34.414 --> 00:29:35.688
<i>So I've heard.</i>

804
00:29:35.689 --> 00:29:39.619
We stopped by David Gallo's
apartment to get a scent sample.

805
00:29:39.620 --> 00:29:41.033
Reva. have a close look.

806
00:29:41.034 --> 00:29:43.343
I want to show you what
picking up after a dog-

807
00:29:43.344 --> 00:29:45.379
<i>really looks like.</i>

808
00:29:45.482 --> 00:29:46.310
[Rex sniffing]

809
00:29:46.310 --> 00:29:47.310
Track it!

810
00:29:48.931 --> 00:29:50.000
♪
[suspenseful music]

811
00:29:53.620 --> 00:29:54.688
Oh!

812
00:29:54.689 --> 00:29:55.379
Yeah cute.

813
00:29:55.379 --> 00:29:56.103
He does tricks.

814
00:29:56.103 --> 00:29:56.793
Okay okay.

815
00:29:56.794 --> 00:29:57.827
Get him out of my rental.

816
00:30:00.793 --> 00:30:02.274
Picking up the
scent of a dead man.

817
00:30:02.275 --> 00:30:04.000
<i>That is a pretty cool trick.</i>

818
00:30:06.931 --> 00:30:08.655
We have CCTV footage-

819
00:30:09.620 --> 00:30:11.171
<i>of you accepting-</i>

820
00:30:11.172 --> 00:30:13.067
this package from Avery Creehan.

821
00:30:13.068 --> 00:30:14.412
Right here.

822
00:30:14.413 --> 00:30:15.757
Charlie: <i>We expected to find it
ditched somewhere in the area.</i>

823
00:30:15.758 --> 00:30:17.654
But you were kind
enough to hang on to it.

824
00:30:17.655 --> 00:30:18.861
What was inside?

825
00:30:18.862 --> 00:30:21.447
Just some papers
for my services.

826
00:30:21.448 --> 00:30:22.448
What are you getting at?

827
00:30:23.413 --> 00:30:25.033
Reva. we can take this
back to my lab to confirm.

828
00:30:25.034 --> 00:30:26.378
Or you can come clean.

829
00:30:26.379 --> 00:30:27.757
<i>Did the Defense give you-</i>

830
00:30:27.758 --> 00:30:29.931
something of David
Gallo's to test?

831
00:30:32.172 --> 00:30:35.102
I think you and I need
to go somewhere private.

832
00:30:35.103 --> 00:30:36.310
I want to talk this over.

833
00:30:45.896 --> 00:30:47.481
I knew you couldn't have
pulled David's identity-

834
00:30:47.482 --> 00:30:48.550
from that evidence.

835
00:30:48.551 --> 00:30:49.723
You lied!

836
00:30:49.724 --> 00:30:51.067
I didn't.

837
00:30:51.068 --> 00:30:54.826
I told you I tested
what they gave me.

838
00:30:54.827 --> 00:30:57.378
You falsified
evidence on the stand.

839
00:30:57.379 --> 00:30:59.723
And was David Gallo not
the man in the fire?

840
00:30:59.724 --> 00:31:02.136
Didn't your little dog just
confirm that that was true?

841
00:31:02.137 --> 00:31:03.481
But how did he get there?

842
00:31:03.482 --> 00:31:05.136
<i>A criminal is about to-</i>

843
00:31:05.137 --> 00:31:06.999
let an innocent man
burn for his crimes.

844
00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:08.440
You're okay with
letting that happen?

845
00:31:10.931 --> 00:31:12.034
I made a call for you.

846
00:31:12.793 --> 00:31:14.343
What call?

847
00:31:14.344 --> 00:31:16.412
There's a senior forensic
associate position-

848
00:31:16.413 --> 00:31:17.827
waiting for you in Toronto.

849
00:31:17.931 --> 00:31:18.862
<i>Better hours.</i>

850
00:31:18.863 --> 00:31:19.895
<i>Better pay.</i>

851
00:31:19.896 --> 00:31:20.999
<i>And best of all-</i>

852
00:31:21.000 --> 00:31:22.000
none of this.

853
00:31:22.344 --> 00:31:24.067
Once court adjourns-

854
00:31:24.068 --> 00:31:26.309
you don't have to take
the case home with you.

855
00:31:26.310 --> 00:31:27.378
<i>Sarah. what do you think-</i>

856
00:31:27.379 --> 00:31:29.309
<i>is going to happen
in court tomorrow?</i>

857
00:31:29.310 --> 00:31:31.136
I know that you can't
prove any of this.

858
00:31:31.137 --> 00:31:33.217
Otherwise you wouldn't be
chasing after me right now.

859
00:31:35.448 --> 00:31:37.208
I guess I'll just have
to take the stand and-

860
00:31:38.551 --> 00:31:40.034
tell the truth.

861
00:31:41.551 --> 00:31:44.482
Don't you think the truth
is for the jury to decide?

862
00:31:45.655 --> 00:31:46.655
You're right.

863
00:31:50.103 --> 00:31:51.344
I'll see you in the morning.

864
00:32:08.310 --> 00:32:10.240
Hey. you headed to the trial?

865
00:32:10.241 --> 00:32:11.792
Yeah.

866
00:32:11.793 --> 00:32:13.033
Nothing more we can do now.

867
00:32:13.034 --> 00:32:15.205
Yeah sometimes it's worse
to have half the story-

868
00:32:15.206 --> 00:32:16.240
and no way to prove it.

869
00:32:16.241 --> 00:32:17.481
It's frustrating-

870
00:32:17.482 --> 00:32:19.654
to be stuck in limbo
after all this effort.

871
00:32:19.655 --> 00:32:21.585
Well I'll just have
to take the stand-

872
00:32:21.586 --> 00:32:25.586
and tell the jury I wasn't
able to replicate the tests.

873
00:32:25.689 --> 00:32:27.275
♪
[mysterious music]

874
00:32:29.862 --> 00:32:31.172
[Rex barking]

875
00:32:31.586 --> 00:32:33.309
Charlie: <i>What's up?</i>

876
00:32:33.310 --> 00:32:34.793
What is it?

877
00:32:34.896 --> 00:32:36.861
[Rex barking]

878
00:32:36.862 --> 00:32:38.413
He's got something.

879
00:32:38.931 --> 00:32:39.793
[Rex barking]

880
00:32:39.794 --> 00:32:40.826
He must be tracking
David's remains-

881
00:32:40.827 --> 00:32:42.930
from the scents
in his apartment.

882
00:32:42.931 --> 00:32:45.171
Charlie. this is the
debris that I sorted out-

883
00:32:45.172 --> 00:32:47.092
looking for bone samples
that we may have missed.

884
00:32:47.724 --> 00:32:48.724
[Rex barks]

885
00:32:48.965 --> 00:32:50.620
There's got to be something.

886
00:32:52.379 --> 00:32:53.482
Good job pal.

887
00:33:16.758 --> 00:33:18.274
Charlie: <i>Sarah. I need
you to come with me.</i>

888
00:33:18.275 --> 00:33:19.172
<i>I think there's a way-</i>

889
00:33:19.173 --> 00:33:20.205
to save this case after all.

890
00:33:20.206 --> 00:33:21.206
Rex.

891
00:33:29.724 --> 00:33:30.724
[Rex barks]

892
00:33:33.344 --> 00:33:34.895
That substrate definitely
looks like a match-

893
00:33:34.896 --> 00:33:36.274
to what we've got in the morgue.

894
00:33:36.275 --> 00:33:38.068
There's also something in there.

895
00:33:46.793 --> 00:33:48.275
You might need to dig it out.

896
00:33:55.172 --> 00:33:56.172
<i>Oh.</i>

897
00:33:57.379 --> 00:33:59.619
Well I only know two men
who'd wear a ring this flashy.

898
00:33:59.620 --> 00:34:01.481
And I don't think it
belongs to Harry Styles.

899
00:34:01.482 --> 00:34:03.758
I think David was drowned
by Gene right here.

900
00:34:05.517 --> 00:34:07.379
That's going to
be hard to prove.

901
00:34:08.000 --> 00:34:09.620
I think I have an
idea where to start.

902
00:34:10.896 --> 00:34:11.931
[Rex barks]

903
00:34:19.482 --> 00:34:20.379
Donovan: <i>Your honour.</i>

904
00:34:20.380 --> 00:34:21.481
<i>It's not every day-</i>

905
00:34:21.482 --> 00:34:23.378
you get to see the rationale
for a warrant firsthand.

906
00:34:23.379 --> 00:34:24.826
Make it quick.

907
00:34:24.827 --> 00:34:27.723
So we suspect that the body of
David Gallo was transported-

908
00:34:27.724 --> 00:34:29.654
<i>in a vehicle
somewhere on this lot.</i>

909
00:34:29.655 --> 00:34:30.826
If we're right-

910
00:34:30.827 --> 00:34:32.447
Rex should be able to lead
us right to that vehicle.

911
00:34:32.448 --> 00:34:33.137
All right Rex.

912
00:34:33.137 --> 00:34:34.137
<i>Track it.</i>

913
00:34:35.482 --> 00:34:36.793
♪
[suspenseful music]

914
00:34:42.896 --> 00:34:45.309
♪
[mysterious music]

915
00:34:45.310 --> 00:34:46.344
[Rex sniffing]

916
00:34:56.000 --> 00:34:57.758
[Rex barks]

917
00:35:04.655 --> 00:35:05.758
Thank you.

918
00:35:06.172 --> 00:35:06.862
Hey.

919
00:35:06.863 --> 00:35:08.412
I need you guys down here now.

920
00:35:08.413 --> 00:35:09.689
Okay.

921
00:35:10.448 --> 00:35:11.137
What's going on here?

922
00:35:11.137 --> 00:35:12.000
<i>I need you to stall-</i>

923
00:35:12.001 --> 00:35:13.826
for as long as you can.

924
00:35:13.827 --> 00:35:14.964
Sarah. this is it.

925
00:35:14.965 --> 00:35:15.965
We're out of time.

926
00:35:15.966 --> 00:35:17.688
Look. you asked us to
get you a conviction.

927
00:35:17.689 --> 00:35:18.793
I can get you the evidence.

928
00:35:19.586 --> 00:35:20.896
You just need to trust me.

929
00:35:22.344 --> 00:35:24.034
Yeah. I trust you.

930
00:35:26.551 --> 00:35:27.551
Thank you.

931
00:35:34.689 --> 00:35:36.862
[Rex barks]

932
00:35:46.310 --> 00:35:47.999
You guys better not be
hanging me out to dry.

933
00:35:48.000 --> 00:35:48.758
No no.

934
00:35:48.759 --> 00:35:49.919
Sarah knows what she's doing.

935
00:36:05.724 --> 00:36:07.585
♪
[suspenseful music]

936
00:36:07.586 --> 00:36:08.551
Don't hover.

937
00:36:08.552 --> 00:36:09.896
I'm not hovering.

938
00:36:11.482 --> 00:36:12.724
Rex.

939
00:36:13.862 --> 00:36:15.620
[Rex whines]

940
00:36:16.482 --> 00:36:20.655
Science demands patience.

941
00:36:25.517 --> 00:36:26.620
Clerk: <i>All rise!</i>

942
00:36:29.655 --> 00:36:30.724
Good morning.

943
00:36:31.103 --> 00:36:31.793
Welcome back.

944
00:36:31.794 --> 00:36:34.033
<i>Court is now in session.</i>

945
00:36:34.034 --> 00:36:34.862
[judge bangs gavel]

946
00:36:34.863 --> 00:36:36.655
Clerk: <i>Please take your seats.</i>

947
00:36:39.241 --> 00:36:41.000
[Jesse texting]

948
00:36:42.931 --> 00:36:44.378
[Jesse sighs]

949
00:36:44.379 --> 00:36:45.482
[phone pings]

950
00:36:49.310 --> 00:36:50.724
[Rex barks]

951
00:36:54.793 --> 00:36:57.309
We're not ready for
closing arguments?

952
00:36:57.310 --> 00:36:58.103
Your honour.

953
00:36:58.104 --> 00:37:00.964
In light of last
week's revelation-

954
00:37:00.965 --> 00:37:06.068
I motion to call
a final witness.

955
00:37:06.724 --> 00:37:07.620
Granted.

956
00:37:07.621 --> 00:37:10.757
I call Jesse Mills to the stand.

957
00:37:10.758 --> 00:37:11.758
What?

958
00:37:14.068 --> 00:37:15.275
[Jesse texting]

959
00:37:18.172 --> 00:37:19.481
[phone beeps]

960
00:37:19.482 --> 00:37:21.137
♪
[dramatic music]

961
00:37:21.241 --> 00:37:22.241
[phone pings]

962
00:37:23.551 --> 00:37:24.551
Find Jesse.

963
00:37:32.758 --> 00:37:37.481
Jesse Mills. what exactly
is your role at the SJPD?

964
00:37:37.482 --> 00:37:40.551
Well. I'm a Fourth
Class Constable.

965
00:37:41.620 --> 00:37:43.067
And Tech Analyst.

966
00:37:43.068 --> 00:37:44.654
Like-you know.

967
00:37:44.655 --> 00:37:46.413
A tech detective.

968
00:37:51.517 --> 00:37:53.205
A tech-tective. I say sometimes.

969
00:37:53.206 --> 00:37:54.103
Avery: <i>Objection.</i>

970
00:37:54.104 --> 00:37:56.550
This witness has no
relevance to the case.

971
00:37:56.551 --> 00:37:57.792
No. let me get to it.

972
00:37:57.793 --> 00:37:58.551
I'm relevant!

973
00:37:58.655 --> 00:37:59.735
[in distance] <i>I'm relevant!</i>

974
00:38:05.551 --> 00:38:06.551
Okay I'll tell you why.

975
00:38:07.689 --> 00:38:08.930
A team needs a foundation.

976
00:38:08.931 --> 00:38:10.689
<i>And some would say-</i>

977
00:38:10.793 --> 00:38:12.136
<i>that analysts are invaluable.</i>

978
00:38:12.137 --> 00:38:13.274
<i>People call me
lightning fingers.</i>

979
00:38:13.275 --> 00:38:14.275
[Rex barks]

980
00:38:17.034 --> 00:38:18.172
[crowd exclaims]

981
00:38:18.482 --> 00:38:19.793
[banging gavel] Order!

982
00:38:21.448 --> 00:38:22.620
[banging gavel] Order!

983
00:38:25.172 --> 00:38:26.654
Good boy.

984
00:38:26.655 --> 00:38:27.655
Michael: <i>Thanks.</i>

985
00:38:31.689 --> 00:38:35.205
Your honour. I'd like
to recall a witness.

986
00:38:35.206 --> 00:38:36.378
<i>Dr. Truong.</i>

987
00:38:36.379 --> 00:38:37.654
<i>Were you able to
generate a test-</i>

988
00:38:37.655 --> 00:38:39.343
that positively
ID'd David Gallo?

989
00:38:39.344 --> 00:38:40.344
I was.

990
00:38:40.345 --> 00:38:44.585
I submit the following
as Exhibit 73-B.

991
00:38:44.586 --> 00:38:45.861
Sarah: <i>Now these results-</i>

992
00:38:45.862 --> 00:38:47.241
<i>did not come from
the arson site.</i>

993
00:38:48.551 --> 00:38:50.378
My colleague.
Dr. Karma Poole and I-

994
00:38:50.379 --> 00:38:53.757
both tried to replicate
Dr. Warner's results-

995
00:38:53.758 --> 00:38:55.136
<i>to little success.</i>

996
00:38:55.137 --> 00:38:56.930
<i>In fact-</i>

997
00:38:56.931 --> 00:38:58.275
it's impossible.

998
00:38:59.241 --> 00:39:00.999
Michael: <i>How do you reckon
Dr. Warner was able-</i>

999
00:39:01.000 --> 00:39:01.931
to present those results-

1000
00:39:01.932 --> 00:39:04.205
to this court. last week.

1001
00:39:04.206 --> 00:39:06.964
She would have required a
stronger sample to test-

1002
00:39:06.965 --> 00:39:07.931
as I had here-

1003
00:39:07.932 --> 00:39:09.758
<i>with this sample.</i>

1004
00:39:09.862 --> 00:39:12.619
And where did your sample
come from Dr. Truong?

1005
00:39:12.620 --> 00:39:15.274
From the trunk of
the defendant's car-

1006
00:39:15.275 --> 00:39:16.481
collected just this morning.

1007
00:39:16.482 --> 00:39:17.757
<i>Which was found-</i>

1008
00:39:17.758 --> 00:39:19.205
<i>along with mineral-
enriched water-</i>

1009
00:39:19.206 --> 00:39:20.654
<i>from the aquarium in which-</i>

1010
00:39:20.655 --> 00:39:21.826
David was drowned.

1011
00:39:21.827 --> 00:39:22.827
Avery: <i>Objection!</i>

1012
00:39:23.379 --> 00:39:24.792
Overruled.

1013
00:39:24.793 --> 00:39:26.861
Sarah: <i>David Gallo couldn't
have set that fire.</i>

1014
00:39:26.862 --> 00:39:28.895
He wasn't alive-

1015
00:39:28.896 --> 00:39:31.241
when he reached the
nightclub with Gene Powell.

1016
00:39:31.344 --> 00:39:32.516
♪
[dramatic music]

1017
00:39:32.517 --> 00:39:34.517
[observers murmur]

1018
00:39:35.586 --> 00:39:36.413
[Rex barks]

1019
00:39:36.414 --> 00:39:37.757
[judge bangs gavel]

1020
00:39:37.758 --> 00:39:39.343
I want to see all the attorneys-

1021
00:39:39.344 --> 00:39:40.412
in my chamber.

1022
00:39:40.413 --> 00:39:41.413
Now!

1023
00:39:48.689 --> 00:39:49.827
♪
[soft music]

1024
00:39:54.793 --> 00:39:55.793
Michael: <i>Hey.</i>

1025
00:39:58.379 --> 00:39:59.792
You should have seen Avery-

1026
00:39:59.793 --> 00:40:01.172
shaking like a leaf.

1027
00:40:02.310 --> 00:40:04.999
Unsurprisingly. Gene
change his plea.

1028
00:40:05.000 --> 00:40:06.171
But given what's come to light-

1029
00:40:06.172 --> 00:40:07.932
we are pursuing first-
degree murder charges.

1030
00:40:08.655 --> 00:40:09.275
Wow.

1031
00:40:09.276 --> 00:40:10.412
<i>Yeah.</i>

1032
00:40:10.413 --> 00:40:13.205
<i>I hope you'll be available
to testify then too.</i>

1033
00:40:13.206 --> 00:40:15.585
Well that almost
sounds like an apology.

1034
00:40:15.586 --> 00:40:16.448
<i>But it's just-</i>

1035
00:40:16.448 --> 00:40:17.413
[Michael chuckles]

1036
00:40:17.413 --> 00:40:18.379
missing something.

1037
00:40:18.380 --> 00:40:19.517
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

1038
00:40:20.137 --> 00:40:21.206
Sarah.

1039
00:40:21.758 --> 00:40:23.000
I'm sorry for doubting you.

1040
00:40:23.862 --> 00:40:24.551
There it is.

1041
00:40:24.551 --> 00:40:25.551
<i>Yeah.</i>

1042
00:40:27.655 --> 00:40:30.412
Yeah. I'll admit that-

1043
00:40:30.413 --> 00:40:32.896
<i>it hasn't been easy to-</i>

1044
00:40:34.448 --> 00:40:37.344
<i>adjust to a working
relationship.</i>

1045
00:40:38.931 --> 00:40:39.931
We'll get there.

1046
00:40:48.413 --> 00:40:50.068
I'll take the stand
whenever you need.

1047
00:40:54.413 --> 00:40:55.241
[Michael sighs]

1048
00:40:55.242 --> 00:40:56.482
[door opening]

1049
00:40:58.000 --> 00:40:59.136
[door closing]

1050
00:40:59.137 --> 00:41:00.068
Donvoan: <i>We couldn't have
solved this without you.</i>

1051
00:41:00.069 --> 00:41:01.274
Lewis: <i>Oh!</i>

1052
00:41:01.275 --> 00:41:02.688
That's what I've been trying
to tell you all along.

1053
00:41:02.689 --> 00:41:04.102
Nice of you to admit it.

1054
00:41:04.103 --> 00:41:06.033
Which is why I'm
giving the Powell case-

1055
00:41:06.034 --> 00:41:07.412
back over to Financial Crimes.

1056
00:41:07.413 --> 00:41:08.792
With Major Crimes on hand-

1057
00:41:08.793 --> 00:41:10.585
to assist if you
need us. of course.

1058
00:41:10.586 --> 00:41:12.516
You guys have been chasing
this guy long enough.

1059
00:41:12.517 --> 00:41:15.136
Your team deserves to take
it across the finish line.

1060
00:41:15.137 --> 00:41:17.378
Thank you.
Superintendent Donovan.

1061
00:41:17.379 --> 00:41:18.930
[Lewis chuckles]

1062
00:41:18.931 --> 00:41:21.343
I just hope that there
are no hard feelings-

1063
00:41:21.344 --> 00:41:22.862
when the chief
job comes calling.

1064
00:41:27.448 --> 00:41:29.309
Well that was the
right thing to do-

1065
00:41:29.310 --> 00:41:30.379
taking the hit.

1066
00:41:31.827 --> 00:41:33.787
You know what the chief
loves more than a big win?

1067
00:41:34.724 --> 00:41:36.895
Interdepartmental collaboration.

1068
00:41:36.896 --> 00:41:38.447
♪
[upbeat music]

1069
00:41:38.448 --> 00:41:40.137
The race for the
job is not over.

1070
00:41:46.724 --> 00:41:49.688
Well. the Judge is
throwing out my testimony-

1071
00:41:49.689 --> 00:41:51.343
<i>after that little display.</i>

1072
00:41:51.344 --> 00:41:53.551
So I guess we're
even now. Truong.

1073
00:41:53.655 --> 00:41:55.965
Uh. for what?

1074
00:41:57.034 --> 00:41:59.114
Getting the high paying job
over you back in the day.

1075
00:41:59.965 --> 00:42:01.136
Not that it matters now.

1076
00:42:01.137 --> 00:42:03.343
But since you mentioned it-

1077
00:42:03.344 --> 00:42:05.206
Sutherland Schmidt offered
me that internship.

1078
00:42:06.344 --> 00:42:07.793
I turned it down.

1079
00:42:08.931 --> 00:42:11.171
Sour grapes. Sarah.

1080
00:42:11.172 --> 00:42:12.172
That's not a great look.

1081
00:42:13.517 --> 00:42:14.482
I'm serious Reva.

1082
00:42:14.483 --> 00:42:16.275
I'm not interested in payback.

1083
00:42:17.793 --> 00:42:19.826
I'm a scientist-

1084
00:42:19.827 --> 00:42:21.412
<i>which is why I've reported you-</i>

1085
00:42:21.413 --> 00:42:24.654
to the Society of Canadian
Forensic Analysts-

1086
00:42:24.655 --> 00:42:27.310
for taking conclusions from
clients and falsifying reports.

1087
00:42:29.689 --> 00:42:31.172
[Rex barks]

1088
00:42:32.275 --> 00:42:33.620
Okay wow!

1089
00:42:34.827 --> 00:42:36.241
If that's how you
want to play it-

1090
00:42:37.862 --> 00:42:39.000
I will see you in court.

1091
00:42:39.689 --> 00:42:40.689
Not likely!

1092
00:42:41.413 --> 00:42:42.826
[Rex barks]

1093
00:42:42.827 --> 00:42:44.033
That must have felt good.

1094
00:42:44.034 --> 00:42:46.930
You have no idea!

1095
00:42:46.931 --> 00:42:48.965
[they laugh]

1096
00:42:50.310 --> 00:42:51.688
Thanks Rex.

1097
00:42:51.689 --> 00:42:52.689
Hey.

1098
00:42:54.758 --> 00:42:57.068
♪
[soft music]

1099
00:42:57.758 --> 00:43:00.758
♪
[closing theme music]

1100
00:43:01.305 --> 00:44:01.198
